**Idea — accumulate runs**: Iterate; for each run of identical chars, append the char then (if run > 1) its count.

```javascript
function compressProductCode(s) {
  let out = '';
  let i = 0;
  while (i < s.length) {
    let j = i;
    while (j < s.length && s[j] === s[i]) j++;
    out += s[i];
    if (j - i > 1) out += String(j - i);
    i = j;
  }
  return out.length < s.length ? out : s;
}
```

**Time**: O(n). **Space**: O(n).

Note: the catch is the count-greater-than-9 case ('a12' = a twelve times) — multi-digit lengths just append naturally. The final shorter-than check ensures we never make things worse.

