editorial:
**Why length-prefix wins**: Any delimiter you pick could legally appear in a message. Length-prefix removes that ambiguity — the decoder reads `len`, then `#`, then exactly `len` chars.

```javascript
function encodeDecode(msgs) {
  // encode
  let enc = '';
  for (const m of msgs) enc += m.length + '#' + m;
  // decode
  const out = [];
  let i = 0;
  while (i < enc.length) {
    let j = i;
    while (enc[j] !== '#') j++;
    const len = parseInt(enc.slice(i, j), 10);
    out.push(enc.slice(j + 1, j + 1 + len));
    i = j + 1 + len;
  }
  return out;
}
```

**Time**: O(N) where N = total chars. **Space**: O(N).

