editorial:
**Key — gap signature**: For string `s`, build the tuple `((s[i+1]-s[i]) mod 26)` for each adjacent pair. Two strings shift to each other iff their gap tuples are equal.

```javascript
function groupShifted(strs) {
  const groups = new Map();
  for (const s of strs) {
    const key = [];
    for (let i = 1; i < s.length; i++) {
      key.push(((s.charCodeAt(i) - s.charCodeAt(i-1)) % 26 + 26) % 26);
    }
    const k = key.join(',');
    if (!groups.has(k)) groups.set(k, []);
    groups.get(k).push(s);
  }
  const out = [];
  for (const arr of groups.values()) { arr.sort(); out.push(arr); }
  out.sort((a, b) => a[0] < b[0] ? -1 : a[0] > b[0] ? 1 : 0);
  return out;
}
```

**Time**: O(N*K). **Space**: O(N*K). The mod-26 with `+26 % 26` handles the wrap (e.g., 'az' → gap 25; 'ba' → gap (-1+26)%26 = 25).

