**Idea — fixed-size window with char counts**: Maintain two 26-length arrays: `need` (counts in p) and `have` (counts in current window of length |p|). Slide the window one char at a time; compare arrays.

```javascript
function findAnagrams(s, p) {
  const out = [];
  if (p.length > s.length) return out;
  const need = new Array(26).fill(0), have = new Array(26).fill(0);
  for (const c of p) need[c.charCodeAt(0) - 97]++;
  for (let i = 0; i < s.length; i++) {
